http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/BSP-workers-stage-protest/article14009351.ece

Bahujan Samaj Party (BSP) members on Tuesday staged a protest on the Bengaluru-Mysuru highway here over the suicide of Rohith Vemula, a Dalit research scholar at the Hyderabad Central University (HCU).They staged a demonstration at Sri Nalwadi Krishnaraja Wadiyar Circle here . They claimed that the voices of Dalits and backward class students were being crushed by Vice-Chancellors, who were handpicked by the BJP and the RSS. The protesters raised slogans against Prime Minister Narendra Modi, Union Ministers Bandaru Dattatreya and Smriti Irani, and HCU Vice-Chancellor Appa Rao. The protesters demanded the sacking of the Ministers and Mr. Rao.